title.rendered: Renegades vs Stars, Australian T20 League 2022: Today’s Match Preview, Fantasy Cricket Tips

content.rendered:
We have opted for a fantasy cricket team based on the recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable XIs

Fawad Ahmed replaces Marcus Haris in the Renegades squad.

Renegades: Martin Guptill, Jonathan Wells, Sam Harper (wk), Aaron Finch (c), Jonathan Wells, Matthew Critchley, Will Sutherland, Fawad Ahmed, Ruwantha Kellepotha, Tom Rogers, Kane Richardson

Stars: Joe Clarke (wk), Thomas Rogers, Hilton Cartwright, Beau Webster, Nick Larkin, James Seymour, Clint Hinchliffe, Nathan Coulter-Nile, Luke Wood, Liam Hatcher, Adam Zampa (c)

Pitch Report

Venue: Docklands Stadium, Melbourne

(Based on the last 3 games)

1st innings average score: 164

2nd innings average score: 165

Wickets per innings: 6

Type: Balanced

Wins

Batting 1st: 100%

Batting 2nd: —

Fantasy Tips of the Day

In the last three games at the Docklands Stadium, the top order has generated the bulk of the fantasy points.

The pacers have not had much success in the powerplay. Only 28% of wickets fell in the first six overs.

Aaron Finch knows every nook and cranny of the venue. He has blasted 1,476 runs, including a hundred and 12 fifties. On the bowling front, Kane Richardson’s 33 wickets in 23 games top the list.

Sam Harper was the captain of the Ultimate Team in the previous game here, smashing 89 off 48.

In the contests between these teams, Adam Zampa is the highest wicket-taker. He has taken 17 wickets in 13 T20s, maintaining an economy of 6.4.

Renegades have power hitters in their armoury, and more importantly, they have batters who have great numbers at the venue. On the other hand, Stars have been inconsistent in all departments.
